          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between a value proposition and a tagline?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A tagline is a short, often abstract brand slogan. A value proposition is functional and specific — it tells the customer what they get, for whom, and why it's different. A value proposition drives conversions; a tagline drives brand recall. They serve different purposes and should not be confused.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the Steve Blank value proposition formula?</span>
